  <bioghist encodinganalog="545"> 
    <head>Biography of Ernest Emery Harmon</head><p>Ernest Emery Harmon (1893-1933) was an aviator in the Air Corps of the United States. He joined the Air Corps in 1917. In 1919 he piloted the first flight around the rim of the continental United States, a trip that took three months to complete. In 1932 Harmon was commissioned a captain. He was killed jumping from an airplane in 1933. Ernest Harmon Air Force Base in Newfoundland was named for him in 1949.</p>
	 
  </bioghist> 
  <scopecontent encodinganalog="520"> 
    <head>Scope and Content</head><p>The collection contains biographical information about Harmon and his family; photographs of Harmon, his family, and colleagues; newspaper clippings about the 1919 around-the-rim flight; and speeches from the dedication of Harmon Air Force Base.</p>
	 
  </scopecontent> 
